37PacketBuffer::Packet::Packet(const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
38 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header)
39 : marker_bit(rtp_packet.Marker()),
40 payload_type(rtp_packet.PayloadType()),
41 seq_num(rtp_packet.SequenceNumber()),
42 timestamp(rtp_packet.Timestamp()),
43 times_nacked(-1),
44 video_header(video_header) {}
45
46PacketBuffer::PacketBuffer(size_t start_buffer_size, size_t max_buffer_size)
47 : max_size_(max_buffer_size),
48 first_seq_num_(0),
49 first_packet_received_(false),
50 is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_(false),
51 buffer_(start_buffer_size),
52 sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_(false) {
53 RTC_DCHECK_LE(start_buffer_size, max_buffer_size);
54 // Buffer size must always be a power of 2.
55 RTC_DCHECK((start_buffer_size & (start_buffer_size - 1)) == 0);
56 RTC_DCHECK((max_buffer_size & (max_buffer_size - 1)) == 0);
57}
58
59PacketBuffer::~PacketBuffer() {
60 Clear();
61}
62
63PacketBuffer::InsertResult PacketBuffer::InsertPacket(
64 std::unique_ptr<PacketBuffer::Packet> packet) {
65 PacketBuffer::InsertResult result;
66
67 uint16_t seq_num = packet->seq_num;
68 size_t index = seq_num % buffer_.size();
69
70 if (!first_packet_received_) {
71 first_seq_num_ = seq_num;
72 first_packet_received_ = true;
73 } else if (AheadOf(first_seq_num_, seq_num)) {
74 // If we have explicitly cleared past this packet then it's old,
75 // don't insert it, just silently ignore it.
76 if (is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_) {
77 return result;
78 }
79
80 first_seq_num_ = seq_num;
81 }
82
83 if (buffer_[index] != nullptr) {
84 // Duplicate packet, just delete the payload.
85 if (buffer_[index]->seq_num == packet->seq_num) {
86 return result;
87 }
88
89 // The packet buffer is full, try to expand the buffer.
90 while (ExpandBufferSize() && buffer_[seq_num % buffer_.size()] != nullptr) {
91 }
92 index = seq_num % buffer_.size();
93
94 // Packet buffer is still full since we were unable to expand the buffer.
95 if (buffer_[index] != nullptr) {
96 // Clear the buffer, delete payload, and return false to signal that a
97 // new keyframe is needed.
98 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Clear PacketBuffer and request key frame.";
99 ClearInternal();
100 result.buffer_cleared = true;
101 return result;
102 }
103 }
104
105 packet->continuous = false;
106 buffer_[index] = std::move(packet);
107
108 UpdateMissingPackets(seq_num);
109
110 result.packets = FindFrames(seq_num);
111 return result;
112}
113
114void PacketBuffer::ClearTo(uint16_t seq_num) {
115 // We have already cleared past this sequence number, no need to do anything.
116 if (is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_ &&
117 AheadOf<uint16_t>(first_seq_num_, seq_num)) {
118 return;
119 }
120
121 // If the packet buffer was cleared between a frame was created and returned.
122 if (!first_packet_received_)
123 return;
124
125 // Avoid iterating over the buffer more than once by capping the number of
126 // iterations to the |size_| of the buffer.
127 ++seq_num;
128 size_t diff = ForwardDiff<uint16_t>(first_seq_num_, seq_num);
129 size_t iterations = std::min(diff, buffer_.size());
130 for (size_t i = 0; i < iterations; ++i) {
131 auto& stored = buffer_[first_seq_num_ % buffer_.size()];
132 if (stored != nullptr && AheadOf<uint16_t>(seq_num, stored->seq_num)) {
133 stored = nullptr;
134 }
135 ++first_seq_num_;
136 }
137
138 // If |diff| is larger than |iterations| it means that we don't increment
139 // |first_seq_num_| until we reach |seq_num|, so we set it here.
140 first_seq_num_ = seq_num;
141
142 is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_ = true;
143 auto clear_to_it = missing_packets_.upper_bound(seq_num);
144 if (clear_to_it != missing_packets_.begin()) {
145 --clear_to_it;
146 missing_packets_.erase(missing_packets_.begin(), clear_to_it);
147 }
148}
149
150void PacketBuffer::Clear() {
151 ClearInternal();
152}
153
154PacketBuffer::InsertResult PacketBuffer::InsertPadding(uint16_t seq_num) {
155 PacketBuffer::InsertResult result;
156 UpdateMissingPackets(seq_num);
157 result.packets = FindFrames(static_cast<uint16_t>(seq_num + 1));
158 return result;
159}
160
161void PacketBuffer::ForceSpsPpsIdrIsH264Keyframe() {
162 sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_ = true;
163}
164
165void PacketBuffer::ClearInternal() {
166 for (auto& entry : buffer_) {
167 entry = nullptr;
168 }
169
170 first_packet_received_ = false;
171 is_cleared_to_first_seq_num_ = false;
172 newest_inserted_seq_num_.reset();
173 missing_packets_.clear();
174}
175
176bool PacketBuffer::ExpandBufferSize() {
177 if (buffer_.size() == max_size_) {
178 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "PacketBuffer is already at max size (" << max_size_
179 << "), failed to increase size.";
180 return false;
181 }
182
183 size_t new_size = std::min(max_size_, 2 * buffer_.size());
184 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Packet>> new_buffer(new_size);
185 for (std::unique_ptr<Packet>& entry : buffer_) {
186 if (entry != nullptr) {
187 new_buffer[entry->seq_num % new_size] = std::move(entry);
188 }
189 }
190 buffer_ = std::move(new_buffer);
191 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "PacketBuffer size expanded to " << new_size;
192 return true;
193}
194
195bool PacketBuffer::PotentialNewFrame(uint16_t seq_num) const {
196 size_t index = seq_num % buffer_.size();
197 int prev_index = index > 0 ? index - 1 : buffer_.size() - 1;
198 const auto& entry = buffer_[index];
199 const auto& prev_entry = buffer_[prev_index];
200
201 if (entry == nullptr)
202 return false;
203 if (entry->seq_num != seq_num)
204 return false;
205 if (entry->is_first_packet_in_frame())
206 return true;
207 if (prev_entry == nullptr)
208 return false;
209 if (prev_entry->seq_num != static_cast<uint16_t>(entry->seq_num - 1))
210 return false;
211 if (prev_entry->timestamp != entry->timestamp)
212 return false;
213 if (prev_entry->continuous)
214 return true;
215
216 return false;
217}
218
219std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PacketBuffer::Packet>> PacketBuffer::FindFrames(
220 uint16_t seq_num) {
221 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PacketBuffer::Packet>> found_frames;
222 for (size_t i = 0; i < buffer_.size() && PotentialNewFrame(seq_num); ++i) {
223 size_t index = seq_num % buffer_.size();
224 buffer_[index]->continuous = true;
225
226 // If all packets of the frame is continuous, find the first packet of the
227 // frame and add all packets of the frame to the returned packets.
228 if (buffer_[index]->is_last_packet_in_frame()) {
229 uint16_t start_seq_num = seq_num;
230
231 // Find the start index by searching backward until the packet with
232 // the |frame_begin| flag is set.
233 int start_index = index;
234 size_t tested_packets = 0;
235 int64_t frame_timestamp = buffer_[start_index]->timestamp;
236
237 // Identify H.264 keyframes by means of SPS, PPS, and IDR.
238 bool is_h264 = buffer_[start_index]->codec() == kVideoCodecH264;
239 bool has_h264_sps = false;
240 bool has_h264_pps = false;
241 bool has_h264_idr = false;
242 bool is_h264_keyframe = false;
243 int idr_width = -1;
244 int idr_height = -1;
245 while (true) {
246 ++tested_packets;
247
248 if (!is_h264 && buffer_[start_index]->is_first_packet_in_frame())
249 break;
250
251 if (is_h264) {
252 const auto* h264_header = absl::get_if<RTPVideoHeaderH264>(
253 &buffer_[start_index]->video_header.video_type_header);
254 if (!h264_header || h264_header->nalus_length >= kMaxNalusPerPacket)
255 return found_frames;
256
257 for (size_t j = 0; j < h264_header->nalus_length; ++j) {
258 if (h264_header->nalus[j].type == H264::NaluType::kSps) {
259 has_h264_sps = true;
260 } else if (h264_header->nalus[j].type == H264::NaluType::kPps) {
261 has_h264_pps = true;
262 } else if (h264_header->nalus[j].type == H264::NaluType::kIdr) {
263 has_h264_idr = true;
264 }
265 }
266 if ((sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_ && has_h264_idr && has_h264_sps &&
267 has_h264_pps) ||
268 (!sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_ && has_h264_idr)) {
269 is_h264_keyframe = true;
270 // Store the resolution of key frame which is the packet with
271 // smallest index and valid resolution; typically its IDR or SPS
272 // packet; there may be packet preceeding this packet, IDR's
273 // resolution will be applied to them.
274 if (buffer_[start_index]->width() > 0 &&
275 buffer_[start_index]->height() > 0) {
276 idr_width = buffer_[start_index]->width();
277 idr_height = buffer_[start_index]->height();
278 }
279 }
280 }
281
282 if (tested_packets == buffer_.size())
283 break;
284
285 start_index = start_index > 0 ? start_index - 1 : buffer_.size() - 1;
286
287 // In the case of H264 we don't have a frame_begin bit (yes,
288 // |frame_begin| might be set to true but that is a lie). So instead
289 // we traverese backwards as long as we have a previous packet and
290 // the timestamp of that packet is the same as this one. This may cause
291 // the PacketBuffer to hand out incomplete frames.
292 // See: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=7106
293 if (is_h264 && (buffer_[start_index] == nullptr ||
294 buffer_[start_index]->timestamp != frame_timestamp)) {
295 break;
296 }
297
298 --start_seq_num;
299 }
300
301 if (is_h264) {
302 // Warn if this is an unsafe frame.
303 if (has_h264_idr && (!has_h264_sps || !has_h264_pps)) {
304 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
305 << "Received H.264-IDR frame "
306 "(SPS: "
307 << has_h264_sps << ", PPS: " << has_h264_pps << "). Treating as "
308 << (sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_ ? "delta" : "key")
309 << " frame since WebRTC-SpsPpsIdrIsH264Keyframe is "
310 << (sps_pps_idr_is_h264_keyframe_ ? "enabled." : "disabled");
311 }
312
313 // Now that we have decided whether to treat this frame as a key frame
314 // or delta frame in the frame buffer, we update the field that
315 // determines if the RtpFrameObject is a key frame or delta frame.
316 const size_t first_packet_index = start_seq_num % buffer_.size();
317 if (is_h264_keyframe) {
318 buffer_[first_packet_index]->video_header.frame_type =
319 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
320 if (idr_width > 0 && idr_height > 0) {
321 // IDR frame was finalized and we have the correct resolution for
322 // IDR; update first packet to have same resolution as IDR.
323 buffer_[first_packet_index]->video_header.width = idr_width;
324 buffer_[first_packet_index]->video_header.height = idr_height;
325 }
326 } else {
327 buffer_[first_packet_index]->video_header.frame_type =
328 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
329 }
330
331 // If this is not a keyframe, make sure there are no gaps in the packet
332 // sequence numbers up until this point.
333 if (!is_h264_keyframe && missing_packets_.upper_bound(start_seq_num) !=
334 missing_packets_.begin()) {
335 return found_frames;
336 }
337 }
338
339 const uint16_t end_seq_num = seq_num + 1;
340 // Use uint16_t type to handle sequence number wrap around case.
341 uint16_t num_packets = end_seq_num - start_seq_num;
342 found_frames.reserve(found_frames.size() + num_packets);
343 for (uint16_t i = start_seq_num; i != end_seq_num; ++i) {
344 std::unique_ptr<Packet>& packet = buffer_[i % buffer_.size()];
345 RTC_DCHECK(packet);
346 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(i, packet->seq_num);
347 // Ensure frame boundary flags are properly set.
348 packet->video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame = (i == start_seq_num);
349 packet->video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame = (i == seq_num);
350 found_frames.push_back(std::move(packet));
351 }
352
353 missing_packets_.erase(missing_packets_.begin(),
354 missing_packets_.upper_bound(seq_num));
355 }
356 ++seq_num;
357 }
358 return found_frames;
359}
360
361void PacketBuffer::UpdateMissingPackets(uint16_t seq_num) {
362 if (!newest_inserted_seq_num_)
363 newest_inserted_seq_num_ = seq_num;
364
365 const int kMaxPaddingAge = 1000;
366 if (AheadOf(seq_num, *newest_inserted_seq_num_)) {
367 uint16_t old_seq_num = seq_num - kMaxPaddingAge;
368 auto erase_to = missing_packets_.lower_bound(old_seq_num);
369 missing_packets_.erase(missing_packets_.begin(), erase_to);
370
371 // Guard against inserting a large amount of missing packets if there is a
372 // jump in the sequence number.
373 if (AheadOf(old_seq_num, *newest_inserted_seq_num_))
374 *newest_inserted_seq_num_ = old_seq_num;
375
376 ++*newest_inserted_seq_num_;
377 while (AheadOf(seq_num, *newest_inserted_seq_num_)) {
378 missing_packets_.insert(*newest_inserted_seq_num_);
379 ++*newest_inserted_seq_num_;
380 }
381 } else {
382 missing_packets_.erase(seq_num);
383 }
384}
